# Restructure snippets/critical-css.liquid — template-gated sections

## Background

CC investigation (ujg6.37, 2026-05-20) found:
- File: snippets/critical-css.liquid — 38.6 KB, 459 CSS rules, single minified line
- Coverage audit: 95% unused on brand mobile (/collections/davines)
- Only ~6.9 KB (body + universal utilities, bytes 32546–39564) is truly ATF-critical sitewide
- Remaining 31.7 KB is template-specific CSS bundled sitewide

## Section map (from byte-position analysis)

| Section | Bytes | Templates that need it | Gate |
|---|---|---|---|
| Swiper carousel | 2.6 KB (0–2634) | index, collection | `{% if template contains 'index' or template contains 'collection' %}` |
| Banner slider | 1.1 KB (2634–3775) | index only | `{% if template contains 'index' %}` |
| Flickity + search + inputs | 4 KB (3775–7843) | Mixed — inputs universal, Flickity product/collection, search=search | Split: keep inputs universal, gate Flickity + search |
| Accordion + tabs | 2.3 KB (7843–10222) | product, article | `{% if template contains 'product' or template contains 'article' %}` |
| Breadcrumb + product page | 3.8 KB (10222–14064) | product, collection | `{% if template contains 'product' or template contains 'collection' %}` |
| Collection filters + sidebar + product grid | 4.7 KB (14064–18873) | collection | `{% if template contains 'collection' %}` |
| SATCB + remaining | 13.4 KB (18873–32546) | product, cart | Audit selectors in this range; gate appropriately |
| Body + universal utils | 6.9 KB (32546–39564) | ALL | Keep always-inline |

## Required steps

1. **Run prettier/postcss on the minified file** to get formatted, one-rule-per-line output. Do NOT use any transformation that changes selector specificity or rule order.

2. **Audit the `SATCB + remaining` block** (bytes 18873–32546, 13.4 KB) — it's the largest unknown section. Extract its selectors and map each to a template. Likely contains product-grid, collection, and some PDP-specific rules mixed together.

3. **Reorganize the file** into Liquid-gated sections:
   ```liquid
