OC paid tier: glm-5.1:cloud (senior-developer). This is bulk CSS reorganization — pattern recognition across 459 rules + mechanical regrouping. Not judgment-heavy; OC excels at this.

description:
## Context
Parent ticket hairmnl-theme-tyio identified LoyaltyLion as the primary
cause of cart INP poor events. The SDK fires two scripts on cart load
(326ms + 212ms = 538ms CPU), then makes an API call to
platform.loyaltylion.com. When the API responds (~20-30s into load), a
~400ms long task fires — directly in the window when users tap cart
buttons (quantity change, remove, checkout). Result: 15.9% poor INP.

## Goal
Apply the same createElement override pattern used for Reamaze (meu epic,
commit cc8d92d pattern) to defer LoyaltyLion initialization on /cart
specifically until the user's first interaction. The rewards display
(points balance, tier) can appear ~200-500ms after first tap — acceptable
CX delay for a loyalty feature.

## Design

1. Identify the LoyaltyLion script trigger. In layout/theme.liquid or a
   LoyaltyLion app embed, the SDK is loaded via Shopify's content_for_header
   or a direct <script> tag. Audit to confirm.

2. If app embed (content_for_header injected): use the document.createElement
   override pattern:
   ```js
   const _orig = document.createElement.bind(document);
   document.createElement = function(tag) {
     const el = _orig(tag);
     if (tag.toLowerCase() === 'script') {
       const origSrcDesc = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(HTMLScriptElement.prototype, 'src');
       Object.defineProperty(el, 'src', {
         set(v) {
           if (v && v.includes('loyaltylion.net') && !window.__ll_defer_released) {
             window.__ll_deferred_src = v;
             return;
           }
           origSrcDesc.set.call(this, v);
         },
         get() { return origSrcDesc.get.call(this); }
       });
     }
     return el;
   };
   // Release on first interaction
   ['click','touchstart','keydown'].forEach(ev =>
     document.addEventListener(ev, function release() {
       window.__ll_defer_released = true;
       document.removeEventListener(ev, release);
       if (window.__ll_deferred_src) {
         const s = document.createElement('script');
         document.createElement = _orig; // restore before injecting
         s.src = window.__ll_deferred_src;
         document.head.appendChild(s);
       }
     }, {once: true, passive: true})
   );
   ```

3. Scope the guard to /cart only (check `window.location.pathname === '/cart'`
   or Liquid condition `{% if request.path == '/cart' %}`).

4. Verify CX: after applying the guard, the loyalty points widget should
   still appear within 500ms of first tap. If the widget is above the
   fold and users expect to see their points immediately, this is an
   acceptable delay.

## Acceptance criteria
- LoyaltyLion scripts (sdk.loyaltylion.net) do NOT load on initial /cart
  page load for users who haven't interacted yet (verify via Lighthouse
  network waterfall: no loyaltylion.net request in first 10s).
- Loyalty widget appears within 500ms of first user interaction on cart.
- Cart PSI mobile TBT improves by ≥400ms (from 1,707ms toward 1,300ms).
- Cart INP poor rate in GA4 RUM drops from 15.9% to <8% within 7d.
- No increase in LoyaltyLion-related CS tickets ("my points aren't showing").

## Scope
≤2 files (layout/theme.liquid + possibly a new snippets/ll-cart-defer.liquid).
≤50 LoC. OC free-tier appropriate after design review.

