**Collection sort dropdown broken on branded sub-collection pages** — discovered during bd 76m9 audit.

## Root cause

`snippets/collection-sorting-custom.liquid` (used by `sections/collection-branded-subcollection.liquid`, used by `templates/collection.branded-subcollection.liquid`) contains jQuery `$()` syntax:

```js
$(function() {
  $('#SortBy').val('{{ collection.sort_by | default: collection.default_sort_by }}')
    .bind('change', function() {
      Shopify.queryParams.sort_by = jQuery(this).val();
      location.search = jQuery.param(Shopify.queryParams);
    });
});
```

Pre-P4, jQuery was loaded via `jquery.min.js` defer in `layout/theme.liquid`. P4 wave-a dropped that — the new comment at theme.liquid says: *"P8 ships a single bundled theme.js that doesn't need jQuery"*.

But the legacy snippet was never refactored. The section setting `collection_sorting` gates the include, so it only fires when the merchant enables sort on a branded subcollection. When that fires, the JS throws `ReferenceError: $ is not defined` and the sort dropdown silently does nothing.

## Impact

Customer clicks a sort option on a `*.branded-subcollection` collection page → nothing happens. Page does not re-sort, URL does not update.

Lower impact than the unstyled CSS bugs because:
- Only one section type (`collection-branded-subcollection`)
- Gated by `section.settings.collection_sorting` setting (merchant has to enable it)
- Other collection templates (collection.absolutrepair, collection.kerastase, etc.) use different sections

But still a real interaction bug. P2.

## Fix options

**Option A — Inline vanilla JS replacement (preferred):**

```js
const sortEl = document.getElementById('SortBy');
if (sortEl) {
  sortEl.value = '{{ collection.sort_by | default: collection.default_sort_by }}';
  sortEl.addEventListener('change', function() {
    const params = new URLSearchParams(location.search);
    params.set('sort_by', this.value);
    location.search = params.toString();
  });
}
```

3 lines shorter, zero deps, works everywhere. Same UX.

**Option B — Re-add jQuery globally** — bigger blast radius, costs ~30KB, contradicts the P8 architectural decision.

Pick A. The replacement is mechanical.

## Verification

1. Find a published collection assigned `collection.branded-subcollection` template (operator: which collections use this?). If none, the bug is theoretical — but the fix should still ship to prevent future activation issues.
2. Change sort dropdown — verify URL updates with `?sort_by=...` and page re-sorts.
3. Test on mobile + desktop, Safari + Chrome.

## Side-finding (file follow-up if confirmed)

Also broken (jQuery-using, but currently orphan):
- `snippets/membership-product-callbacks.liquid` — in TAE allowlist as moved to TAE, so probably moot, but verify the TAE replacement is in place.
- `snippets/wsg-dependencies.liquid` — wsg-* is in DEAD allowlist (8i17 will delete), so moot.

If membership TAE is missing, file as separate ticket.

## Scope

- Single file edit: `snippets/collection-sorting-custom.liquid` (~20 lines replaced)
- Stream A (live push if template is in active use)
- No theme.liquid wiring change

