In snippets/cart-drawer.liquid line 58-60, the left_to_spend amount is computed as:
  {% capture left_to_spend %}
    <span data-left-to-spend>{{ limit_currency | minus: cart.total_price | money_without_trailing_zeros }}</span>
  {% endcapture %}

No lower-bound clamp — when cart.total_price > limit_currency, the result is negative ('₱-1,150'). The .cart__message-default span renders this verbatim.

Low-effort fix in Liquid:
  {% assign left_amount = limit_currency | minus: cart.total_price %}
  {% if left_amount < 0 %}{% assign left_amount = 0 %}{% endif %}
  {% capture left_to_spend %}
    <span data-left-to-spend>{{ left_amount | money_without_trailing_zeros }}</span>
  {% endcapture %}

Also need to mirror the clamp in JS (theme.js:1762):
  const leftToSpend = themeCurrency.formatMoney(Math.max(0, this.cartFreeLimitShipping - this.shippingAmount), theme.moneyFormat);

Note: this is a band-aid. The real visibility issue is that the default span shouldn't be visible at all when cart qualifies (separate bug — see paired ticket on the dual-message rendering).
